The paper deals with an online packing problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves minimizing the number of bins used, which is a combinatorial optimization problem and falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also presents competitive analysis of various algorithms, which is a common technique in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses probabilistic arguments and techniques from machine learning, which fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM), respectively.
